00:20:41.180 --> 00:20:44.100
WILLIAM B. BONVILLIAN:
This is Egils Milbergs

00:20:44.100 --> 00:20:47.490
and I'm not going spend
a lot of time on it.

00:20:47.490 --> 00:20:50.240
But again, it's one of these
indirect factors that turns out

00:20:50.240 --> 00:20:52.520
to have some significance here.

00:20:52.520 --> 00:20:59.150
His point is the old economy
was a world of tangible assets.

00:20:59.150 --> 00:21:03.440
What counted were your plant,
your equipment, your land,

00:21:03.440 --> 00:21:07.040
your physical resources,
your product inventory,

00:21:07.040 --> 00:21:12.000
your infrastructure, support
system, physical stuff.

00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:16.170
In the 21st century
of a new economy,

00:21:16.170 --> 00:21:23.050
intellectual and intangible
assets, those are key.

00:21:23.050 --> 00:21:28.030
So we have a wonderful 19th
century accounting system.

00:21:28.030 --> 00:21:29.500
It's really wonderful.

00:21:29.500 --> 00:21:32.080
Can really value
the old economy.

00:21:32.080 --> 00:21:36.858
It really can't value
the new economy.

00:21:36.858 --> 00:21:39.400
And we've been discussing this
whole problem with the ability

00:21:39.400 --> 00:21:42.400
to get capital on the advances.

00:21:42.400 --> 00:21:45.850
If you've got an
accounting system that

00:21:45.850 --> 00:21:51.193
can't value true value in the
new economy, then of course

00:21:51.193 --> 00:21:53.110
you're going to have a
serious problem getting

00:21:53.110 --> 00:21:55.840
capital funding available.

00:21:55.840 --> 00:21:58.210
So here's an indirect
thing, you know,

00:21:58.210 --> 00:22:01.270
the accounting
system, that turns out

00:22:01.270 --> 00:22:03.860
to have a fairly
significant effect.

00:22:03.860 --> 00:22:09.250
So the inability to
measure intangibles

00:22:09.250 --> 00:22:11.170
undermines the
willingness of firms

00:22:11.170 --> 00:22:14.260
to invest in innovation
because they can't really

00:22:14.260 --> 00:22:17.770
score it and get gains from it,
and it limits the investment

00:22:17.770 --> 00:22:20.880
flow into innovation
as a result.

00:22:20.880 --> 00:22:23.290
So, and he argues,
paints a picture,

00:22:23.290 --> 00:22:27.910
of how this intangible
process came about,

00:22:27.910 --> 00:22:34.090
arguing that by the late 90s,
looking at the US economy

00:22:34.090 --> 00:22:36.520
overall, it was about
$1.1 trillion invest

00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:40.090
in intangible assets in
the manufacturing sector.

00:22:40.090 --> 00:22:42.670
In that same sector, there
was a trillion dollars in

00:22:42.670 --> 00:22:46.240
combined in R&D business
processes and software.

00:22:46.240 --> 00:22:49.180
Much more intangible.

00:22:49.180 --> 00:22:53.740
And intangible
capital, he argues,

00:22:53.740 --> 00:22:57.520
became 82% of US
firms' market value,

00:22:57.520 --> 00:23:00.700
just an overwhelming portion
of their market value.

00:23:00.700 --> 00:23:03.310
So we need new
metrics for how firms

00:23:03.310 --> 00:23:09.400
invest in these qualitative
innovation factors,

00:23:09.400 --> 00:23:12.220
so that we can drive
investment in an efficient way

00:23:12.220 --> 00:23:15.070
and to the right places and
we just don't have them.

00:23:15.070 --> 00:23:16.780
We only measure a
couple of things.

00:23:16.780 --> 00:23:19.570
We measure total
company R&D investment--

00:23:19.570 --> 00:23:21.940
that gets reported
on quarterly reports,

00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:24.220
and we get company
patent filings--

00:23:24.220 --> 00:23:25.810
that gets revealed as well.

00:23:25.810 --> 00:23:28.068
But then all this other
stuff, and maybe these

00:23:28.068 --> 00:23:29.110
aren't the right factors.

00:23:29.110 --> 00:23:30.777
Maybe some of them
are completely wrong.

00:23:30.777 --> 00:23:33.350
But there's a whole set of
other potential measures

00:23:33.350 --> 00:23:37.360
we don't even ask for,
or even think about how

00:23:37.360 --> 00:23:38.610
they could be best organized.

00:23:38.610 --> 00:23:44.280
So that's Egils core idea here.

00:23:44.280 --> 00:23:46.780
That's why you need to get some
of these indirect innovation

00:23:46.780 --> 00:23:49.720
factors right, along
with the direct ones.

00:23:49.720 --> 00:23:52.330
Another example.

00:23:52.330 --> 00:23:56.710
This was Udayan
