ignore growth theory,

00:58:49.170 --> 00:58:51.660
you see it right
in front of you.

00:58:51.660 --> 00:58:57.370
So Schultze is out of
classical economics.

00:58:57.370 --> 00:59:00.650
He keeps pointing us to
Japan's success story

00:59:00.650 --> 00:59:04.280
being the national savings rate.

00:59:04.280 --> 00:59:08.390
Solow says it's useful,
